## Naming
- Use explicit and meaningful names.
- Boolean variables use `is/has/can/should` prefixes.
- Domain terminology must follow documented glossary.
- Abbreviations only if team-approved.

## Type System
- `any` is forbidden.
- Prefer explicit typing.
- Separate server response types from UI models.
- Avoid type assertions (`as`) unless unavoidable.

## Structure
- Separate business logic from UI logic.
- Components follow single responsibility principle.
- Pure function principle applies to utils and calculation logic.
- Hooks, effects, and mutations may include side effects.

## Imports
- Use absolute imports.
- Follow layer dependency rules.
- Circular dependencies are forbidden.
